headline: Arista Networks (NYSE:ANET) Stock Dips 11% After Board Member Changes
summary: Arista Networks (NYSE:ANET) recently expanded its Board of Directors, appointing Greg Lavender as a new member and saw the resignation of senior executive John McCool. The company also launched new AI networking capabilities like Cluster Load Balancing and CV UNO to enhance AI workloads. Despite these announcements, Arista's stock price declined by 11% last week, a move in line with broader market pressures; the Nasdaq fell 8% and the S&P 500 dropped 6%, reflecting concerns over potential...
